      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "thinly sliced"
    },
    {
      "name": "green onions",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "thinly sliced"
    },
    {
      "name": "sesame seeds",
      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the sesame oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the ferment-kimchi and cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.",
    "Add the dashi broth, cranberry juice, and soy sauce to the saucepan and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Add the cooked Japanese short grain rice to the saucepan and stir to combine.",
    "Cook for an additional 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until the rice is well coated with the cranberry mixture.",
    "Stir in the pickled ginger, green onions, and sesame seeds.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Serve the ochazuke hot, garnished with additional green onions and sesame seeds if desired."
  ],
